{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1365,"text":"I have a two-year-old daughter named Naya"},{"time":3866,"text":"who is under the mistaken impression"},{"time":5756,"text":"that this conference\nis named in honor of her father."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9343,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":10666,"text":"Who am I to contradict my baby girl?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":13675,"text":"As many of you know, there's something\nabout becoming a parent"},{"time":17569,"text":"that concentrates the mind\non long-term problems like climate change."},{"time":22584,"text":"It was the birth of my daughter\nthat inspired me"},{"time":25073,"text":"to launch this climate organization,"},{"time":27651,"text":"in order to counteract the excessive\npolarization of this issue"},{"time":31546,"text":"in the United States,"},{"time":32879,"text":"and to find a conservative\npathway forward."},{"time":38150,"text":"Yes, folks, a Republican\nclimate solution is possible,"},{"time":42807,"text":"and you know what?"},{"time":44156,"text":"It may even be better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":46512,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":48147,"text":"Let me try to prove that to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51269,"text":"What we really need\nis a killer app to climate policy."},{"time":55867,"text":"In the technology world, a killer app\nis an application so transformative"},{"time":60308,"text":"that it creates its own market,"},{"time":61811,"text":"like Uber."},{"time":63400,"text":"In the climate world,"},{"time":65051,"text":"a killer app is a new\nsolution so promising"},{"time":70000,"text":"that it can break through\nthe seemingly insurmountable"},{"time":73571,"text":"barriers to progress."},{"time":75456,"text":"These include the psychological barrier."},{"time":79005,"text":"Climate advocates have long\nbeen encouraging their fellow citizens"},{"time":82242,"text":"to make short-term sacrifices now"},{"time":84176,"text":"for benefits that accrue to other people"},{"time":86237,"text":"in other countries 30 or 40\nyears in the future."},{"time":89605,"text":"It just doesn't fly because it runs\ncontrary to basic human nature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":94687,"text":"Next is the geopolitical barrier."},{"time":98024,"text":"Under the current rules of global trade,"},{"time":100316,"text":"countries have a strong incentive\nto free ride off the emissions reductions"},{"time":104686,"text":"of other nations,"},{"time":105969,"text":"instead of strengthening\ntheir own programs."},{"time":108225,"text":"This has been the curse"},{"time":109807,"text":"of every international\nclimate negotiations, including Paris."},{"time":114423,"text":"Finally, we have the partisan barrier."},{"time":117502,"text":"Even the most committed countries --"},{"time":119597,"text":"Germany, the United Kingdom, Canada --"},{"time":122821,"text":"are nowhere near reducing emissions\nat the required scale and speed."},{"time":127566,"text":"Not even close."},{"time":129058,"text":"And the partisan climate divide\nis far more acute"},{"time":133332,"text":"here in the United States."},{"time":135803,"text":"We are fundamentally stuck,"},{"time":137933,"text":"and that is why we need\na killer app of climate policy"},{"time":141517,"text":"to break through each of these barriers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":144750,"text":"I'm convinced that the road\nto climate progress in the United States"},{"time":150442,"text":"runs through the Republican Party"},{"time":153081,"text":"and the business community."},{"time":156252,"text":"So in launching\nthe Climate Leadership Council,"},{"time":159032,"text":"I started by reaching out to a who's who\nof Republican elder statesmen"},{"time":162970,"text":"and business leaders,"},{"time":164184,"text":"including James Baker and George Schultz,"},{"time":167585,"text":"the two most respected Republican\nelder statesmen in America;"},{"time":171729,"text":"Martin Feldstein and Greg Mankiw,"},{"time":173622,"text":"the two most respected\nconservative economists in the country;"},{"time":177288,"text":"and Henry Paulson and Rob Walton,"},{"time":179405,"text":"two of the most successful\nand admired business leaders."},{"time":182398,"text":"Together, we co-authored"},{"time":184723,"text":"\"The Conservative Case\nFor Carbon Dividends.\""},{"time":187811,"text":"This represents the first time"},{"time":190370,"text":"that Republican leaders put forth"},{"time":193985,"text":"a concrete market-based climate solution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196522,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":197927,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199020,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":201647,"text":"We presented our plan at the White House"},{"time":203998,"text":"two weeks after President Trump moved in."},{"time":207645,"text":"Almost every leading\neditorial board in the country"},{"time":211547,"text":"has since endorsed our plan,"},{"time":213818,"text":"and Fortune 100 companies\nfrom a wide range of industries"},{"time":218527,"text":"are now getting behind it."},{"time":220902,"text":"So by now you're probably wondering,"},{"time":222887,"text":"what exactly is this plan?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":225313,"text":"Well, our carbon dividends solution\nis based on four pillars."},{"time":229705,"text":"The first is a gradually\nrising carbon tax."},{"time":233639,"text":"Although capitalism is a wonderful system,"},{"time":236190,"text":"like many operating systems,\nit's prone to bugs,"},{"time":239389,"text":"which, in this case, are called\n\"market failures.\""},{"time":242606,"text":"By far the largest is that\nmarket prices fail to take"},{"time":246152,"text":"social and environmental\ncosts into account."},{"time":249915,"text":"That means every market transaction\nis based on incorrect information."},{"time":255279,"text":"This fundamental bug of capitalism,\nmore than any other single factor,"},{"time":259401,"text":"is to blame for our climate predicament."}]},{"cues":[{"time":262760,"text":"Now in theory, this should be\nan easy problem to fix."},{"time":266095,"text":"Economists agree"},{"time":267485,"text":"that the best solution is to put a price\non the carbon content of fossil fuels,"},{"time":272297,"text":"otherwise known as a carbon tax."},{"time":274595,"text":"This would discourage carbon emissions"},{"time":278347,"text":"in every single economic transaction,"},{"time":280691,"text":"every day of the year."},{"time":282425,"text":"However, a carbon tax by itself\nhas proven to be unpopular"},{"time":287795,"text":"and a political dead end."},{"time":289993,"text":"The answer is to return\nall the money raised"},{"time":293542,"text":"directly to citizens,"},{"time":295858,"text":"in the form of equal monthly dividends."},{"time":299679,"text":"This would transform\nan unpopular carbon tax"},{"time":303235,"text":"into a popular and populist solution,"},{"time":306501,"text":"and it would also solve"},{"time":308349,"text":"the underlying psychological barrier\nthat we discussed,"},{"time":311686,"text":"by giving everyone a concrete benefit\nin the here and now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":317307,"text":"And these benefits would be significant."},{"time":319620,"text":"Assuming a carbon tax rate\nthat starts at 40 dollars per ton,"},{"time":323386,"text":"a family of four would receive\n2,000 dollars per year"},{"time":326833,"text":"from the get-go."},{"time":328643,"text":"According to the US Treasury Department,"},{"time":331639,"text":"the bottom 70 percent of Americans\nwould receive more in dividends"},{"time":336693,"text":"than they would pay\nin increased energy prices."},{"time":340008,"text":"That means 223 million Americans\nwould win economically"},{"time":347025,"text":"from solving climate change."},{"time":349811,"text":"And that --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":350997,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":352076,"text":"is revolutionary,"},{"time":353650,"text":"and could fundamentally\nalter climate politics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":358778,"text":"But there's another\nrevolutionary element here."},{"time":361619,"text":"The amount of the dividend would grow"},{"time":365123,"text":"as the carbon tax rate increases."},{"time":367508,"text":"The more we protect our climate,"},{"time":369608,"text":"the more our citizens benefit."},{"time":371487,"text":"This creates a positive feedback loop,"},{"time":373733,"text":"which is crucial,"},{"time":375287,"text":"because the only way we will reach\nour long-term emission-reduction goals"},{"time":379207,"text":"is if the carbon tax rate\ngoes up every year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":382979,"text":"The third pillar of our program\nis eliminating regulations"},{"time":386969,"text":"that are no longer needed"},{"time":388532,"text":"once a carbon dividends plan is enacted."},{"time":391634,"text":"This is a key selling point\nto Republicans and business leaders."},{"time":399099,"text":"So why should we trade"},{"time":401166,"text":"climate regulations for a price on carbon?"},{"time":403721,"text":"Well, let me show you."},{"time":406176,"text":"Our plan would achieve nearly twice\nthe emissions reductions"},{"time":410628,"text":"of all Obama-era climate\nregulations combined,"},{"time":414808,"text":"and nearly three times the new baseline"},{"time":418442,"text":"after President Trump repeals\nall of those regulations."},{"time":422623,"text":"That assumes a carbon tax\nstarting at 40 dollars per ton,"},{"time":426410,"text":"which translates into roughly\nan extra 36 cents per gallon of gas."},{"time":432062,"text":"Our plan by itself"},{"time":434595,"text":"would meet the high end\nof America's commitment"},{"time":438192,"text":"under the Paris Climate Agreement,"},{"time":440494,"text":"and as you can see,"},{"time":442192,"text":"the emissions reductions\nwould continue over time."},{"time":445701,"text":"This illustrates the power\nof a conservative climate solution"},{"time":451293,"text":"based on free markets\nand limited government."},{"time":454205,"text":"We would end up with less regulation"},{"time":457408,"text":"and far less pollution at the same time,"},{"time":460524,"text":"while helping working-class\nAmericans get ahead."},{"time":464532,"text":"Doesn't that sound like something\nwe could all support?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":467794,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":473903,"text":"The fourth and final pillar of our program\nis a new climate domino effect,"},{"time":478446,"text":"based on border carbon adjustments."},{"time":481124,"text":"Now that may sound complicated,"},{"time":483251,"text":"but it, too, is revolutionary,"},{"time":485140,"text":"because it provides us\na whole new strategy"},{"time":488025,"text":"to reach a global price on carbon,"},{"time":490597,"text":"which is ultimately what we need."},{"time":492488,"text":"Let me show you an example."},{"time":494444,"text":"Suppose Country A adopts\na carbon dividends plan,"},{"time":497969,"text":"and Country B does not."},{"time":499440,"text":"Well, to level the playing field"},{"time":501867,"text":"and protect the competitiveness\nof its industries,"},{"time":505126,"text":"Country A would tax imports from Country B"},{"time":509048,"text":"based on their carbon content."},{"time":510911,"text":"Fair enough."},{"time":512452,"text":"But here's where it gets\nreally interesting,"},{"time":514620,"text":"because the money raised at the border\nwould increase the dividends"},{"time":518282,"text":"going to the citizens of Country A."},{"time":520560,"text":"Well, how long do you think it would take\nthe public in Country B to realize"},{"time":524756,"text":"that that money should be going to them,"},{"time":526713,"text":"and to push for a carbon\ndividends plan in their own land?"},{"time":529726,"text":"Add a few more countries,"},{"time":531249,"text":"and we get a new climate domino effect."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535517,"text":"Once one major country or region\nadopts carbon dividends"},{"time":539830,"text":"with border carbon adjustments,"},{"time":541479,"text":"other countries are compelled\nto follow suit."},{"time":543962,"text":"One by one the dominoes fall."},{"time":546898,"text":"And this domino effect\ncould start anywhere."},{"time":549251,"text":"My preference, strongly,\nis the United States,"},{"time":552685,"text":"but it could also start\nin the United Kingdom,"},{"time":555236,"text":"in Germany or another European country,"},{"time":557468,"text":"or even in China."}]},{"cues":[{"time":560012,"text":"Let's take China as an example."},{"time":562046,"text":"China is committed to reducing\ngreenhouse gas emissions,"},{"time":566614,"text":"but what its leaders care even more about"},{"time":568979,"text":"is transitioning their economy\nto consumer-led economic development."},{"time":573980,"text":"Well, nothing could do more\nto hasten that transition"},{"time":576880,"text":"than giving every Chinese citizen\na monthly dividend."},{"time":580183,"text":"In fact, this is the only policy solution"},{"time":583728,"text":"that would enable China to meet\nits environmental and economic goals"},{"time":587394,"text":"at the same time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":588776,"text":"That's why this is the killer app\nof climate policy,"},{"time":592177,"text":"because it would enable us to overcome"},{"time":595540,"text":"each of the barriers we discussed earlier:"},{"time":597877,"text":"the psychological barrier,\nthe partisan barrier,"},{"time":600985,"text":"and, as we've just seen,\nthe geopolitical barrier."},{"time":604469,"text":"All we need is a country to lead the way."},{"time":608471,"text":"And one method of finding\nwhat you're looking for"},{"time":610924,"text":"is to take out an ad."},{"time":612608,"text":"So let's read this one together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":614611,"text":"Wanted: country to pioneer\ncarbon dividends plan."},{"time":618445,"text":"Cost to country: zero."},{"time":620912,"text":"Starting date: as soon as possible."},{"time":623215,"text":"Advantages: most effective\nclimate solution,"},{"time":626681,"text":"popular and populist,"},{"time":628462,"text":"pro-growth and pro-business,"},{"time":630328,"text":"shrinks government\nand helps the working class."},{"time":635281,"text":"Additional compensation: gratitude\nof current and future generations,"},{"time":641638,"text":"including my daughter."}]},{"cues":[{"time":644211,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":645387,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":652641,"text":"Chris Anderson: Just one\nquestion for you, Ted."},{"time":657401,"text":"I'm actually not sure"},{"time":658576,"text":"I've seen a conservative\nget a standing O at TED before that."},{"time":661497,"text":"That's pretty cool."},{"time":663734,"text":"The logic seems really powerful,"},{"time":665584,"text":"but some people you talk to in politics"},{"time":667678,"text":"say it's hard to imagine this\nstill getting through Congress."},{"time":671773,"text":"How are you feeling\nabout momentum behind this?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":674312,"text":"Ted Halstead: So I understand\nthat many are very pessimistic"},{"time":677961,"text":"about what's happening in\nthe United States with President Trump."},{"time":681034,"text":"I'm less pessimistic; here's why."},{"time":682637,"text":"The actions of this White House,\nthe early actions on climate,"},{"time":685667,"text":"are just the first move\nin a complex game of climate chess."},{"time":691270,"text":"So far it's been a repeal-only strategy;"},{"time":693905,"text":"the pressure is going to mount \nfor a replacement program,"},{"time":696779,"text":"which is where we come in."},{"time":698049,"text":"And there are three reasons why,\nwhich I'll go through real quickly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":701271,"text":"One, the business community\nis fundamentally parting ways"},{"time":704508,"text":"with the White House on climate change."},{"time":706968,"text":"In fact, we're finding"},{"time":708143,"text":"a number of Fortune 100 companies\nsupporting our program."},{"time":711278,"text":"Within two months,\nwe're going to be announcing"},{"time":713501,"text":"some really surprising names\ncoming out in favor of this program."},{"time":716580,"text":"Two, there is no issue\nin American politics"},{"time":719737,"text":"where there's a more fundamental gap\nbetween the Republican base"},{"time":723571,"text":"and the Republican leadership\nthan climate change."},{"time":726230,"text":"And three, thinking of\nthis analogy of chess,"},{"time":731405,"text":"the big decision up ahead is:\nDoes the administration stay in Paris?"},{"time":735658,"text":"Well, let's pan it out both ways."},{"time":737309,"text":"If it stays in Paris, as many\nare pushing for in the administration,"},{"time":741126,"text":"well then that begs a question:\nWhat's the plan?"},{"time":743745,"text":"We have the plan."},{"time":745229,"text":"But if they don't stay in Paris,"},{"time":747324,"text":"the international pressure\nwill be overwhelming."},{"time":749800,"text":"Our Secretary of State will be asking\nother countries for NATO contributions,"},{"time":753451,"text":"and they'll be saying,\n\"No, give us our Paris commitment."},{"time":756377,"text":"Come through on your commitments,\nwe'll come through on ours.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":759313,"text":"So, international, business\nand even the Republican base"},{"time":762631,"text":"will all be calling for\na Republican replacement plan."},{"time":766577,"text":"And, hopefully, we've provided one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769531,"text":"CA: Thank you so much, Ted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":770842,"text":"TH: Thank you, Chris."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772017,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}